## 4. 通用表示学习：intermediate layers 经常比 final layers 更适合 downstream probe

有一篇非常直接的近期工作叫 **Does Representation Matter? Exploring Intermediate Layers in Large Language Models**。它研究 Transformer 和 SSM 中不同层的表示质量，结论就是：**intermediate layers often yield more informative representations for downstream tasks than final layers**，并且文章贡献里明确写“intermediate layers consistently provide better representations for downstream tasks than final layers”。

这给你的 claim 提供了一个非常通用的背景：

> Final-layer representations are optimized for the pretraining / generation objective, not necessarily for auxiliary diagnostic or downstream readout tasks.

你的 GUI grounding probe 就是一个 auxiliary readout task，因此中后层优于最后层并不反常。

