## 8. 这篇文章最强的版本

我建议最终不要写成：

> 我们微调 UI-TARS / UI-Venus / GUI-Owl，提高 grounding。

而写成：

> **We diagnose and bypass the coordinate bottleneck in native GUI agents.**

中文就是：

> 我们诊断并绕过 native GUI agent 中的坐标生成瓶颈。

你可以这样组织全文：

### Problem

Native GUI agents must eventually output executable actions, often as language-visible coordinate tokens. This final coordinate interface may not be the best place to read grounding evidence.

### Observation

Across GUI-AIMA and several coordinate-generating GUI agents, grounding evidence is layer-wise non-monotonic; late-middle layers often provide stronger patch-level localization than final layers.

### Method

Freeze the native agent. Train lightweight layer-wise coordinate-free heads to read spatial posterior from intermediate visual tokens. Fuse layers with a learned readiness selector. Convert posterior to action region or point.

### Application

Use the retrofit as a non-invasive grounding improvement and safety gate for existing GUI agents.

### Value

Low-cost, model-specific heads; no full retraining; no degradation of base policy; better grounding; better debuggability.

